commit.message: Replace deprecated license_file with license_files in setup.cfg

Depend on Levenshtein instead of python-Levenshtein

From
https://github.com/maxbachmann/python-Levenshtein/blob/de2b1d5fcd1d4d8fc376f2c6c9d9f8901e68d14b/README.md,
“The package was renamed to Levenshtein and can be found
[here](https://github.com/maxbachmann/Levenshtein). The
python-Levenshtein package will continue to be updated alongside the new
package”

Update python-Levenshtein GitHub URL

The current URL corresponding to
https://pypi.org/project/python-Levenshtein/ is
https://github.com/maxbachmann/python-Levenshtein.

Remove executable bit from filesystem permissions of README.md

An executable readme makes no sense, of course.
